[[File:Santorini Amoudi Bay.jpg|thumb|Amoudi Bay on the Greek island of Santorini]] '''Amoudi Bay''' is a bay on the Greek Island of [[Santorini]]. The feature is set into the high volcanic cliffs of western Santorini below the town of [[Oia, Greece|Oia]]. == Description == The bay is a well known site on the island<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=http://elle.in/culture/guide-mykonos-santorini-shivan-narresh/|title=The bachelorette's guide to Mykonos and Santorini, according to Shivan & Narresh|last=Team|first=ELLE India|website=Elle India|language=en-US|access-date=2018-08-03}}</ref>, and is often cited as an excellent location for viewing the sunset.<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/a-complete-guide-to-santorini-greece_us_5976c5a4e4b0c6616f7ce4d1|title=A Complete Guide to Santorini, Greece|last=Tourist|first=College|date=2017-07-25|website=Huffington Post|language=en-US|access-date=2018-08-03}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thomascook.com/holidays/greece/santorini/things-to-do/amoudi-bay/|title=Amoudi Bay {{!}} Thomas Cook|work=Thomas Cook|access-date=2018-08-03|language=en-US}}</ref> The bay is also known for the 200 steps leading from the base of the feature to the town of Oia on the cliffs above.<ref name=":0" /> Due to the locale's importance to local tourism, the base of the bay's cliffs is dotted with buildings belonging to the village of Ormos Armeni, and many sailing tours use Amoudi as their staging point.<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":1" />
