{{Orphan|date=October 2016}}
{{Infobox journal | cover = | discipline = Monégasque history | abbreviation = Ann. Monég. | editor = | publisher = | country = | history = 1977-present | frequency = 1/year | impact = | impact-year = | website = | link1 = | link1-name = | link2 = | link2-name = | ISSN = 0257-960X | eISSN = | CODEN = | LCCN = | OCLC = }} '''Annales monégasques''' is a journal of [[History of Monaco|Monégasque history]].
==History== The journal was established in 1977 by [[Franck Biancheri (archivist)|Franck Biancheri]], the archivist of the [[Prince's Palace of Monaco]].<ref name=enquetedupasse>{{cite news|last1=Radoman|first1=Milena|title=En quête du passé|url=http://www.monacohebdo.mc/9160-en-quete-du-passe|accessdate=December 20, 2015|work=[[Monaco Hebdo]]|date=June 21, 2012}}</ref><ref name=lesannalesmonegasquesmatin>{{cite news|title=Les Annales monégasques racontent le Monaco d'antan|url=http://archives.monacomatin.mc/article/culture-et-loisirs/monaco-les-annales-monegasques-racontent-le-monaco-dantan.47394.html|accessdate=December 20, 2015|work=[[Monaco-Matin]]|date=August 9, 2008}}</ref> The first issue included articles on varied topics like [[La Condamine]] in the Middle Ages, Monaco-born music theorist [[Honoré Langlé]], the [[Hymne Monégasque]].<ref name=annalespdf>{{cite web|title=ANNALES MONEGASQUES|url=http://www.palais.mc/medias_upload/vos_fichiers/PDF/sommaire_AM_1-37.pdf|website=Prince's Palace of Monaco|accessdate=December 20, 2015}}</ref>
By 2012, the new editor, [[Thomas Fouilleron]], the new archivist of the Prince's Palace of Monaco, suggested he wanted to digitalize past issues.<ref name=enquetedupasse/>
The 39th issue, published on November 27, 2015, includes articles about the relationship between the [[House of Grimaldi]] and the [[House of Romanov]], the correspondence between [[Prince Pierre, Duke of Valentinois]] and author [[Marcel Proust]], the friendship between [[Albert I, Prince of Monaco]] and composer [[Jules Massenet]], and [[Alexandre Dumas]]'s novel about [[Catherine Charlotte de Gramont]], the wife of [[Louis I, Prince of Monaco]].<ref name=dossierrusse>{{cite web|title=Dossier Russe au sommaire des Annales Monégasques|url=http://www.monacochannel.mc/Chaines/Palais-Princier-de-Monaco/News-Photos/Dossier-Russe-au-sommaire-des-Annales-Monegasques|website=Monaco Channel|publisher=Prince's Palace of Monaco|accessdate=December 20, 2015|date=November 30, 2015}}</ref>
