The '''Declaration of the United Nations Conference on the Human Environment''', or '''Stockholm Declaration''', was adopted June 16, 1972 by the [[United Nations Conference on the Human Environment]] at the 21st plenary meeting as the first document in international [[environmental law]] to recognize the right to a healthy [[environment (biophysical)|environment]]. In the declaration, the nations agreed to accept responsibility for any environmental effects caused by their actions.<ref>{{Cite news|url=|title=Goals for Environment Talks Listed|last=Astrachan|first=Anthony|date=17 March 1972|work=The Washington Post, Times Herald|access-date=|via=}}</ref>
== Breakdown of Declaration == Within the document, seven proclamations cover the global nature of environmental problems and state that they will require extensive cooperation among nations to resolve.<ref name=":0" /> These proclamations conclude that efforts for environmental preservation and improvement will benefit all people and their posterity.<ref name=":0">{{Cite journal|title=Report of the United Nations Conference on the Human Environment|journal=United Nations|volume=A/CONF.48/14/Rev.1}}</ref><ref name=":1">{{Cite web|url=http://www.unep.org/Documents.multilingual/Default.asp?DocumentID=97&ArticleID=1503|title=Stockholm 1972 - Declaration of the United Nations Conference on the Human Environment - United Nations Environment Programme (UNEP)|last=UNEP|website=www.unep.org|access-date=2016-10-22|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=http://webarchive.loc.gov/all/20150314024203/http%3A//www.unep.org/Documents.Multilingual/Default.asp?documentid%3D97%26articleid%3D1503|archivedate=2015-03-14|df=}}</ref> The declaration then states twenty-six principles to guide the nations through their responsibilities. The action plan is split into three categories including an environmental assessment called Earthwatch, environmental management, and 109 supporting measures.<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":1" />
== External links == {{wikisource}} *{{webarchive |url=http://webarchive.loc.gov/all/20150314024203/http%3A//www.unep.org/Documents.Multilingual/Default.asp?documentid%3D97%26articleid%3D1503 |title=Declaration of the United Nations Conference on the Human Environment - full text |date=2015-03-14}} *[http://legal.un.org/avl/ha/dunche/dunche.html Introductory note by Günther Handl, procedural history note and audiovisual material] on the ''Declaration of the United Nations Conference on the Human Environment (Stockholm Declaration)'' in the [http://legal.un.org/avl/historicarchives.html Historic Archives of the United Nations Audiovisual Library of International Law]
