{{Infobox hotel | hotel_name = Muna Hotel | logo = | logo_width = | logo_caption = | image = | image_width = | caption = | pushpin_map =Somalia | location =[[Mogadishu]], [[Somalia]] | pushpin_map_caption=Location in Somalia | address = | chain = | coordinates = {{coord|2|2|22|N|45|20|14|E|display=inline}} | coordinates_type = | opening_date = | closing_date = | developer = | architect = | operator = |owner =Abdullahi Warsame (manager) | number_of_rooms = | number_of_suites = | number_of_restaurants = | floor_area = | floors = | height = | parking = | website = | footnotes = }} '''Muna Hotel''' ({{lang-ar|فندق منى}}, {{lang-so|Funduq Muna}}, {{lang-fr|Hotel Muna}}) is a hotel in [[Mogadishu]], [[Somalia]]. The hotel, located less than a mile from [[Villa Somalia|Somalia's presidential palace]], is a noted conference centre and is regularly used for meetings between government officials and important persons. <Ref name="aljaz">{{cite news|title= Al-Shabab vows 'massive' Somali war |url=http://english.aljazeera.net/news/africa/2010/08/201082464449278785.html|date=24 August 2010|agency=[[Al Jazeera]]}}</ref>
==History== In 2010 it was the centre of [[Muna Hotel attack|a suicide attack]], killing several members of the Somali Parliament amidst the [[Battle of Mogadishu (2010)|fighting that began]] on 23 August.<Ref name="bbc">{{cite news|title=Somali MPs killed in hotel suicide attack|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-africa-11068805|date=24 August 2010|agency=[[BBC News]]}}</ref>
==Architecture== The hotel is located on a street corner and is housed in a three-storey building. The building is painted in mint and pink and has grey shutters.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.washingtontimes.com/news/2010/aug/24/suicide-bomber-attacks-somali-hotel-killing-32/|title=Suicide bomber attacks Somali hotel killing 32|publisher=''[[The Washington Times]]''|date=24 August 2010}}</ref>The two balconies jut out from the building and are painted pink. The logo for Muna Hotel on the side of the hotel is painted in blue and white. The hotel name is given in French as "Hotel Muna" and then in Arabic underneath.
